  <itemBody>
    <div class="grid-row">
      <div class="col-12">
        <h4>Peter is responsible for the party. He has decided that some of the employees from the circus parade also should help in the candy store. Mary works in the cirkus parade, and has gotten mad about Peter's decision. She has written the following message to you.Â <br/>
<img src="forlystelsesparkopg8.png" alt="forlystelsesparkopg8" width="37%"/>Hi. I have just gotten the message from Peter, saying that some of us from the parade also have to help in the candy store. What is he thinking? He can't just decide that out of nowhere. What should I do? Kind regards, Mary</h4>
        <h6>What is it about Peter's decision that has made Mary mad?</h6>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="grid-row">
      <div class="col-12">
        <choiceInteraction responseIdentifier="RESPONSE" shuffle="true" maxChoices="1" minChoices="0" orientation="vertical">
          <simpleChoice identifier="notbyhimself" fixed="false" showHide="show">Peter does not want to do anything himself.</simpleChoice>
          <simpleChoice identifier="notasked" fixed="false" showHide="show">Peter has not asked the staff from the parade, whether they have time to be in the candy store.</simpleChoice>
          <simpleChoice identifier="secretwish" fixed="false" showHide="show">Peter has a secret wish to ruin the parade.</simpleChoice>
          <simpleChoice identifier="dictate" fixed="false" showHide="show">Peter just wants to dictate everything happening.</simpleChoice>
          <simpleChoice identifier="boring" fixed="false" showHide="show">
            <p>Mary thinks that it is boring to sell candy.</p>
          </simpleChoice>
        </choiceInteraction>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="grid-row">
      <div class="col-12">
        <h6>Why do you think that Peter chose to do what he did?</h6>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="grid-row">
      <div class="col-12">
        <choiceInteraction responseIdentifier="RESPONSE_1" shuffle="true" maxChoices="1" minChoices="0" orientation="vertical">
          <simpleChoice identifier="notlottime" fixed="false" showHide="show">The parade does not take up a lot of time. Therefore, Peter thinks they have time to do other tasks.</simpleChoice>
          <simpleChoice identifier="destroy" fixed="false" showHide="show">Peter wants to destroy the parade, because it sounds boring.</simpleChoice>
          <simpleChoice identifier="notalone" fixed="false" showHide="show">Peter does not want to be in the candy store himself.</simpleChoice>
          <simpleChoice identifier="notthougth" fixed="false" showHide="show">Peter has not thought of the fact that it takes long to prepare for a cirkus parade.</simpleChoice>
          <simpleChoice identifier="cancelled" fixed="false" showHide="show">Peter thought that the parade was cancelled.</simpleChoice>
        </choiceInteraction>
      </div>
    </div>
